<div id='main'>
<div id='content'>
<h1>sphinx_search</h1>
<div class='screenshot'>
<a href="/system/screenshots/15/large/Picture_4.png?1262890608"><img alt="Picture_4" src="/system/screenshots/15/medium/Picture_4.png?1262890608" /></a>
</div>
<div style='width: 75%'>
<div class='big'>
<p>Make your content searchable via the excellent Thinking Sphinx. Sphinx Search automatically creates the necessary indexes on your pages and provides a SearchPage subclass to handle the actual search processing without any code on your part.</p>
<p>You get a full set of Radius tags to iterate and display your search results, including pagination for lengthy result sets. Sphinx Search can provide a foundation for indexing your application&#8217;s custom models, as well.</p>
</div>
